<br>
IF KGoC wants to be able to go further with the higher targets like Sev, Trak, Tal, etc, then people need to be ready at moment's notice to gather or someone else in the bracket  will beat you.  I'm amazed Armonia or some other guild didn't take VS while you guys will still looking for people to get to KC.  I know they eventually took him down, but don't know when they started gathering.<br>
<br>
I keep the KCoG channel it its own channel box in the corner of my screen; it's very small.  When I notice &quot;action&quot; in it, I start monitoring it to see if anything is going on.  If I were to keep it with my other channels, I would probably miss everything that is said in KCoG.<br>
<br>
The KCoG leaders -could- keep a list of member guilds nearby and when a major target pops and KCoG is in line for it, have someone ( bseides the raid leader, they wil be busy ) take 5 minutes to send tells to people in those guilds that are online telling those people to alert their guilds in case the chat in KCoG is missed.  This is more of a courtesy than anything, as any who wants to participate needs to take on the responsibility of monitoring the proper channels.<br>
<br>
